# criando grficos

a <- ggplot(filmes, aes(x = averageRating)) +
  geom_density(fill = "lightblue", alpha = 0.5) +
  labs(title = "Distribuio das Avaliaes Mdias", x = "Avaliao Mdia", y = "Densidade") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1))

filtered_filmes <- filmes %>%
  filter(!is.na(averageRating) & !is.na(numVotes)) %>%
  filter(numVotes < 3000000) 

b <- ggplot(filtered_filmes, aes(x = numVotes, y = averageRating)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6, color = "lightblue") + 
  geom_segment(aes(x = 32000, y = 9.4, xend = 32000, yend = 14.4), 
               linetype = 3, color = "red", size = 1) +
  geom_segment(aes(x = 770000, y = 9.4, xend = 770000, yend = 14.4), 
               linetype = 3, color = "red", size = 1) +
  geom_segment(aes(x = 32000, y = 9.4, xend = 770000, yend = 9.4), 
               linetype = 3, color = "red", size = 1) +
  geom_segment(aes(x = 32000, y = 14.4, xend = 770000, yend = 14.4), 
               linetype = 3, color = "red", size = 1) +
  labs(title = "Relao entre Nmero de Votos e Avaliao Mdia",
       x = "Nmero de Votos",
       y = "Avaliao Mdia") +
  scale_x_log10(labels = scales::comma) +
  theme_minimal()

c <- filmes %>%
  group_by(releaseYear) %>%
  summarise(numMovies = n()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = releaseYear, y = numMovies)) +
  geom_line(color = "lightblue") +
  labs(title = "Nmero de Filmes Lanados por Ano", x = "Ano de Lanamento", y = "Nmero de Filmes") +
  theme_minimal()

d <- filmes %>%
  separate_rows(genres, sep =",") %>%
  group_by(genres) %>%
  summarise(numMovies=n(), avgRating=mean(averageRating)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(genres,-numMovies), y=numMovies)) +
    geom_bar(stat="identity", fill="lightblue") +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(title="Gneros mais Populares", x="Gnero", y="Nmero de Filmes") +
    theme_minimal()

filmes <- read.csv2("data.csv", header=TRUE, sep=",")

library(ggplot2)
library(cowplot)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)

a <- ggplot(filmes, aes(x=averageRating)) +
    geom_density(fill="lightblue", alpha=0.5) +
    labs(title="Distribuio das Avaliaes Mdias", x="Avaliao Mdia", y="Densidade")

filtered_filmes <- filmes %>%
    filter(!is.na(averageRating) & !is.na(numVotes)) %>%
    filter(numVotes < 3000000)

b <- ggplot(filtered_filmes, aes(x=numVotes, y=averageRating)) +
    geom_point(alpha=0.6,color="lightblue") + 
    geom_segment(aes(x=32000,y=9.4,xend=32000,yend=14.4), linetype=3,color="red",size=1) +
    geom_segment(aes(x=770000,y=9.4,xend=770000,yend=14.4), linetype=3,color="red",size=1) +
    geom_segment(aes(x=32000,y=9.4,xend=770000,yend=9.4), linetype=3,color="red",size=1) +
    geom_segment(aes(x=32000,y=14.4,xend=770000,yend=14.4), linetype=3,color="red",size=1) +
    labs(title="Relao entre Nmero de Votos e Avaliao Mdia",
         x="Nmero de Votos",
         y="Avaliao Mdia") + 
    scale_x_log10(labels=scales::comma)

c <- filmes %>%
    group_by(releaseYear) %>%
    summarise(numMovies=n()) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x=releaseYear,y=numMovies)) + 
    geom_line(color="lightblue") + 
    labs(title="Nmero de Filmes Lanados por Ano",x="Ano de Lanamento",y="Nmero de Filmes")

d <- filmes %>%
    separate_rows(genres,sep=",") %>%
    group_by(genres) %>%
    summarise(numMovies=n(),avgRating=mean(averageRating)) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x=reorder(genres,-numMovies),y=numMovies)) + 
        geom_bar(stat="identity",fill="lightblue") + 
        coord_flip() + 
        labs(title="Gneros mais Populares",x="Gnero",y="Nmero de Filmes")
